00179  * SRX_IGN_RX_FULL - Ignore RX FIFO backpressure
00180  *
00181  *
00182  * Notes:
00183  * * IGNORE
00184  * If a device can not or should not assert backpressure, then setting DROP
00185  * will force STARVING status on the status channel for all ports.  This
00186  * eliminates any back pressure from N2.
00187  *
00188  * This implies that it's ok drop packets when the FIFOS fill up.
00189  *
00190  * A side effect of this mode is that the TPA Watcher will effectively be
00191  * disabled.  Since the DROP mode forces all TPA lines asserted, the TPA
00192  * Watcher will never find a cycle where the TPA for the selected port is
00193  * deasserted in order to increment its count.
